For longer tables, `rmarkdown::paged_table()` creates a scrollable, paged version, which is more user-friendly than a very long static table.

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(rmarkdown)
mtcars %>% paged_table()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
`````{=html}
